. The Marine Terminal consists of a control platform and a pumping platform.</p>
<p>

The control platform is equipped with a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../923/8286923.xml">
helicopter</link>  pad, living quarters, control room, vessel traffic control station, offices and life support equipment. The pumping platform contains four 7,000-<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../019/14019.xml#xpointer(//*[./st=%22Horsepower_.28hp.29%22])">
hp</link> (5 <link>
MW</link>) <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../617/23617.xml">
pump</link>s, power <invention wordnetid="105633385" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../330/82330.xml">
generator</link></invention>
s, metering and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../351/173351.xml">
laboratory</link> facilities. Crude oil is only handled on the pumping platform where it is measured, sampled, and boosted to shore via a 48-inch (1.2 meter) diameter pipeline. </p>
<p>

